1. NoSQL DB that stores daata in form of doc/dictionary/JSON
2. {
    key: "value"
}
-- Value may include other docs, arrays, arrays of docs

3. Docs are stored in colllections (equivalent of table in SQL) - A collection comprises of numerous docs with 
no strict schema structure like SQL 

- COLLECTION: User
{
    "name": "Ankit",
    "country": "India",
    "place": "place"
}
{
    "name" : "XYZ",
    "mobile" : 6267513926,
    "class" : 6
    "car" : {
        "name" : "Mclaren",
        "model": "720p"
    }
}